"```sql\nSELECT d.forename, d.surname\nFROM lapTimes lt\nJOIN drivers d ON lt.driverId = d.driverId\nORDER BY lt.time ASC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the full names (forename and surname) of the driver who created the shortest lap time ever recorded in a Formula 1 race. It orders the lap times in ascending order to find the shortest time and limits the result to the top record."